 shortened, resulting in evolutionary trajectories more like those of\nyounger EGPs. Motivated by the work of \\citet{jackson08a,jackson08b}, we\nsuggest that this effect could indeed be important in better explaining some\nobserved transit radii.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 May 2008 20:10:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 27 Jul 2008 20:04:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
