dark matter must be\nnon-relativistic (cold). The model predicts a reheating temperature of the\norder of $3\\times 10^6$ GeV, a brane tension of the order of $10^{25}$ GeV$^4$,\nand the obtained composition of the universe is consistent with the\nobservational data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 May 2008 07:14:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 28 May 2008 04:55:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-18"}
