 matter, although at a much lower level (~100-1000\ntimes lower than during the bright outbusts), and that the true quiescence,\ncharacterized by a soft spectrum and a luminosity of a few 1E32 erg/s, observed\nin the past only in a couple of members of this class, is probably a very rare\nstate.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 May 2008 10:28:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
